According to the New York Post, the letter stated: 'Christie and I have talked recently and I have privately apologized to her, but, given the public nature of their divorce and custody battle, I feel a public apology is also appropriate and deserved.

She added: 'Christie was wrongly vilified as being an embittered ex-wife.

'I’m deeply sorry for my part in causing Christie any unnecessary pain.' 

